   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FOURTEEN THE SPIRIT'S WORK ON AND IN</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE BELIEVERS 6 THE TRANSFORMING OF THE SANCTIFYING SPIRIT Scripture Reading: Rom 12:2b; 2 Cor 4:16, 11; Phil 3:10; 2 Cor 3:18b; Phil 3:12-14; Col 3:10-11; Eph 4:16 OUTLINE The Spirit's transforming is the working out of the Spirit's renewing: Transforming is by renewing Rom 12:2b.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Renewing is to deal with the oldness.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Transforming is to bring forth Christ in newness.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Transforming is a metabolism: To bring in the new element the riches of the Triune God embodied in Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>To discharge the old element the rotten things of Adam.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Transforming is a process through death and resurrection: Bringing our old man through the death of Christ 2 Cor 4:16.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Carrying on our new man in the resurrection of Christ 2 Cor 4:11; Phil 3:10.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Through the Lord Spirit 2 Cor 3:18b: Through the pneumatic Christ in resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Through the life-giving Spirit as the reality of the resurrection of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>For the growth and maturity of the seeking believers: By pursuing Christ Phil 3:12.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>By forgetting the things behind and stretching forward to the things before Phil 3:13.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>To reach the goal and gain the prize the experienced Christ Phil 3:14.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>For the constitution of the members of the new man and the building up of the Body of Christ: For the constitution of the members of the new man Col 3:10-11.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>For the building up of the Body of Christ Eph 4:16.</S>
   </TEXT>
